Marriage Family & Human Behavior by Caroline R. S. Lee
MARRIAGE ISSUES FOR THE MEN'S MOVEMENT
As we continue to examine national issues on marriage and family, we examine the men’s movement and a few issues that the movement has pursued in national debates. It is very important to understand the men’s movement and its nature of thinking, which will help AFMH understand its message. As we get started please understand we do not want to write off what the men’s movement is about nor the many men it has impacted in a very positive way. It is our desire that AFMH knows what the men’s movement is about—“What they are about.” More than anything we want AFMH read each description and look at the image of the men’s movement, decide for themselves whether or not it will negatively impact the cause of the children
